		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<div></div>Battleblade,<br><br><i><u><b>Sword and board is not a downward scaling ability.</b></u></i><br><br>Thus, it is not relevant to this thread about <i>downward scaling abilities</i>.<br><br>Second, your previous response to me was pretty much nonsensical random ramblings.<br><br>Zuko,<br><br><blockquote>"The mechanics of knights and warrior differ greatly that I'm totally
surprise about how knight portray themselves as TANKS. For whatever
reason, you should not be tanking as well as me and you SHOULD be using
your spellbook as a <u>compensation</u> for it (those secondary abilities you got, remember?)"<br></blockquote><div></div><br>Oh dear god, a knight portrayed themself as a TANK?!?!?!&nbsp; The horror!<br><br>Oh wait... <i><b>I am a tank</b></i>.<br><br>No, I shouldn't mitigate/avoid as well as you.&nbsp; With shield block, I avoid a bit better.&nbsp; Yes, warriors should get a situational improvement to avoidance to rectify this situation.&nbsp; Yes, <i>warriors DO mitigate better than knights, regardless of what shield or non-shield configuration you consider</i>.&nbsp; The size of the gap only varies.&nbsp; That gap size does not need to increase from its present value.&nbsp; Whatever solution is developed for increasing warrior avoidance, it <b>should not widen the mitigation gap</b>.&nbsp; Yes, I should be using my spellbook to improve my tanking, and I do.<br><br>So was the entire point of your attack on me to say that warriors need more avoidance?<br><br><blockquote>"<span> The problem is you THINK you are entitle to the same survavility and sturdiness than a Warrior has"<br></span></blockquote><span></span>The problem is you THINK we have the same survivability you do.&nbsp; <i><b>You're wrong</b></i>.<br><br>Furthermore, you THINK we want the same survivability you possess.&nbsp; <i><b>You're wrong</b></i>.<br><br>Next question?<br><span></span>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
