		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>You know, I honestly feel bad for Warriors... I was looking forward to a good discussion with Heimdall, who has even had some interesting suggestions in the SK board.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>But BB keeps promoting the Shield Block issue as a downward scaling tool, as if he's going to be able to solo Vindi with it once he gets it because it's this amazing ability that only Knights can employ efficiently.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>A downward scaling tool is one that has a set value... not&nbsp;a percentage.&nbsp; Because as the set value increases, it is more powerful in lower-end content where mob abilities don't grow, whereas a percentage is an upward scaling tool that is more powerful as the mob becomes more powerful.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Lifetaps and Heals are downward scaling tools, their power is greater as the mobs power scales down because their power doesn't decrease if used on a less powerful mob... Defensive, Shield Block, Stuns are upwards scaling because they prevent a greater amount (or percentage) of damage as the power of the mob scales up, but also are LESS powerful abilities against lesser powerful mobs because the percentage stopped is smaller for the same cost.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Consider this a quick lesson in game mechanics, BB, although I'm sure you'll just call it some kind of Knight conspiracy... but please try to understand terms and proposals before going on your next tirade against them.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=790661" target="_blank">
<img src="http://img219.echo.cx/img219/3240/darksig5zj.png" border="0" alt="" /> </a>
							</div>
								
