			<DIV></DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Heimdall-RN wrote:<BR>
<P>What this basically means isn't that knights are broken, what it means is:</P>
<UL>
<LI>Paladins probably need a minor boost.</LI>
<LI>-1DI hasn't scaled at all similar to the increase in spell efficiency</LI>
<LI>This should probably be looked at.</LI>
<LI>Whatever solution is chosen should be a long term self scaling solution that isn't Expanion era or mob DPS dependant.</LI>
<LI>-1DI is the part that's broken, not Paladin heals, or SK Taps.</LI></UL>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Back to the original idea...</P>
<P>DI-1 is an upwards scaling ability... in your equations, for mobs that have DI greater than 160, it only becomes MORE powerful as you've shown it to be a cutoff point.</P>
<P>A downward scaling tool is something that has been something I believe even Frodlin has pushed for for quite some time... and something similar to your aggro+rune ability from PoR&nbsp;scaled down at lower levels would probably be another good solution... not the mini-vie version you have now, because vie blocks&nbsp;a percentage, not a set value...&nbsp;this would probably be something to push for... as it could easily be a rework of an already existing ability.</P>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
