Heimdall-RN wrote:<BR>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Yes, -1DI scales up.&nbsp; But the mob DPS hasn't scaled up anywhere near the way the spell books have.&nbsp; Currently in a group setting Paladins and SK's tank better than warriors.&nbsp;
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Please, don't forget having more skill points in almost every defensive skill, and slightly higher returns on AC... they may not be as visible as lifetaps and heals, but you can't assume that they're not significantly reducing the level of DI to mark the cutoff.&nbsp; Also remember that even with similar channeling skills, tanks are being whacked on significantly more often than the healers.... those heals cannot be significantly relied on as a constant buffer.</P>
<P>Lets also not forget that outside of 'grind' content, are some significantly hard hitting mobs that do indeed hit over 2 and 3k... I can think of quite a few DoD missions where I wish I had a Warrior in our group just so we could continue.&nbsp; In fact, just fought Maru, the Twelfth Born in Relic yesterday in a PoR exploration group... had a Warrior tanking him because he whacks for over 2k.</P>
