</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>WAIT A MINUTE!!!&nbsp; 3.75 seconds is the heal you are making us out to be using all the time while tanking, which 99% of the Paladins you ever ask would blatantly tell you NO WE DON'T.&nbsp; And if you think we are channelling this spell left and right, then go tank with your shammy and channel that spell all the time and call it reliable to heal you when you want it (which would be every cast since you don't cast it if you don't want it).&nbsp; </P>
<P>And as far as Knights getting -1di and Warriors -3di ...... well alot of suggested -1di for knights and -2/3di for Warriors in the past as a gap increaser from non-tanks but then there are a few who disagree and it usually fades away as an idea til it resurfaces again briefly and fades again.&nbsp; It still does nothing as a downward scaling tool since any change to mob di scales upwards rather with mob power.</P>
<P>Runes are the way to go IMO.&nbsp; At mana cost giving a high proc rate defensive proc rune discipline, this would shave a set amount of damage regardless of what the mob does so scales downward nicely and the extra aggro from it would allow you a better option to use less aggro oriented weapons and more DPS oriented weapons.&nbsp; It would still provide use against harder mobs but wouldn't scale with them and could also be used as an aggro increaser while tanking if you don't want to bother so much with Bazu or rather use better DPS weapons until the point that you are grouping with people that do so much DPS that you would be using aggro weapons instead similiar to a Knight being free to use other spells in weaker groups but when they groups gets so strong there is less time devoted to them as more is devoted to aggro the same.<BR></P>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
