<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Heimdall-RN wrote:
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Remember that I'm not talking about spells as a buffer.&nbsp; I'm saying landing even TWO spells negates -1DI.&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>SK Defense caps at 270, warrior Defense caps at 270.&nbsp; Parry Riposte and Dodge are different though&nbsp; 35 of 240, 25 of 235, and 20 of 200 respectively.&nbsp; 15%, 11%, and 10%.</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>So how many more hits would you Dodge, Parry, or Riposte in a given fight, and how much more damage would you avoid through this?&nbsp; How much more damage would be mitigated on average by your higher returns on AC...&nbsp; How faster would you kill the mob by adding more DPS to the group?</P>
<P>This is exactly what I mean by overestimating one persons power, while downplaying your own "total class power."&nbsp; Sure, with straight numbers anyone can just throw things together and say... hey... two of these outweigh one of these.... but there's a lot more variables than what you're posting involved.</P>
