			>
			<div>First, that's absolutely correct, that's why I asked Frodlin for info from his parses on exactly how much difference the skill caps provide.</div><div></div><div>Second. Eh. Avoidance from Sheildblock apparently blows away -1DI. Two casts of spells blows away -1DI. If you don't like the Blast Heals, two HoT's will do about the same, though there may be more mana involved, I haven't done the math there yet.</div><div></div><div>Third: Only a druid or Shaman would make your heals &quot;redundant&quot; even then, heals are heals. With low health agro not even a shaman is going to help like a paladin can. And no, I aint talkin about LoH. I don't care if a paladin can summon an outhouse, if it makes it more efficient to heal him than a warrior, there's a problem. Even if heals are a tertiary role for paladins, even beyond secondary roles, they're still powerful enough to make up enough damage to obliterate the healing efficiency provided by -1DI.</div><div></div><div>Fourth: I could care less about low impact groups. If you're in a group like that, they're taking anyone who'll come, and class balance goes out the window for warm bodies.</div><div></div><div>Fifth is something I've been mentioning for the last several posts. Its entirelylikely that increased skillcaps in Parry, riposte, and dodge along with increased DPS will shorten the fight enough to make up some of that lost ground. The question is how much. I don't think its 100DI worth.</div>	
