		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			There are 3 problems with this thread:<br><br>1. The original poster once read someone post that Wariro tanking advantages do not scale downward and did not understand what was being said.<br><br>When doing weaker content there is a definate limit to the value of greater tanking ability. When Knights are relatively strong for the content they are tanking, they have the mana and the time to apply their secondary capabilities.<br><br>However when a Wariror is relatively strong for the content, he has no real secondary abilities to apply. In weaker content, our main asset -superior tanking has less value. They "cure" is not a rune to *cough* improve our tanking, but rather group friendly abilities or solid DPS in all weapon configurations so we can take care of incoming damage by passive means and focus our effort on DPS.<br><br>The actual problem is that superior tanking does not confer any particular advantage vs. weaker content for Warriors - an observation made by many, includig Knights about Warriors in DoN for example.<br><br>2. Knowing full well that #1 was the actual Warrior issue and not some red herring Warriors need a mini-rune, Knights played along - no doubt amused by Warriors that didn't get it and could by hornswoggled.<br><br>3. The actual "fix" IS as I noted. Warriors to, just like Knights do, take advantage of shields and Shield Block to increase their passive means of reducing damage and to expend their effort in doing DPS with thier disciplines and hopefully with a nice high ratio 1Hander to use with that shield.<br><br>It's sad to see Knights, who know full well what the real issues are, play games with Warriors in their forum.<br><br>I figured you ought to know Heimdall that you were being sold a bills of goods.<div></div>	
