<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=14454#M14454">71</a> of 481
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 724 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			I like the idea of warriors getting some creative abilities that use endurance... scaled appropriately so it's not overly punishing on endurance usage (I know you guys already have a lot of issues with end usage, I'd also like to see the incite line scaled down a bit in endurance usage).&nbsp; Another idea would be a "gather mana" sort of thing for endurance.&nbsp; Come up with a decent role play justification for it, make it an hour or 2 reuse, and boom- you can recover your endurance quickly after death.<br><br>As has been observed, warriors are clearly the superior tank on the very hardest content, due to abilities that readily scale upwards (warrior mitigation advantages can save literally hundereds of dps on a raid boss, before you even toss in defensive).<br><br>However, the same advantages don't necessarily scale down to group content.&nbsp; Shield block would be an ability that scales pretty evenly across all content- it'd save you 8-9% damage on a 200 dps mob, and it'll save you 8-9% of damage on a 2000 dps mob.&nbsp; Superior mitigation, through a shield softcap or the fact you have better returns after cap, are very definitely an upward scaling ability (superior mitigation might save you nothing vs other classes on very weak content, it might save you 10-15% on very difficult content.&nbsp; Improving mitigation over what you have now might save you an additional zilch against weak content, on up to a couple percent vs difficult content).<br><br>The problem is developing abilities that scale downward to group content without breaking balance on higher dps mobs (we saw this happen in gates, to the point knights were not desirable tanks).&nbsp; Abilities that can shave off a fixed amount of dps will be a downward scaling capability (say, for the sake of argument, warriors get a theoretical capability that shaves 40 dps off of every mob, as long as you have endurance to maintain it.&nbsp; That's 20% of a 200 dps mob's damage gone; it's 2% of a 2000 dps mob's damage).&nbsp; An easy way to accomplish this is through defensive procs.&nbsp; Rework shocking defense into something useful (with a correspondingly much lower reuse timer), or introduce a new ability that can provide for the same.<br><div></div>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=175692" target=new>Josahd, Scourge Knight</a>
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
