		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<blockquote>"I do like the idea of knights being at -1DI and warriors at -3 DI. That
would put some&nbsp; noticeable space between warriors and knights and
noticeable space between the three plate tanks and everyone else."<br></blockquote><br>Very, very, very bad idea.&nbsp; Knights don't need increased seperation over other classes at this point in time.&nbsp; This would have several very bad effects:&nbsp; Knights fall waaaaaay behind warriors on difficult content, maintain an advantage on weak content (ie, it doesn't solve the reverse scaling issue), and would result in mobs in future content being developed with that full 15% damage mitigation advantage in mind (keep in mind warriors already have better mitigation, apart from even DI-1.&nbsp; This would result in warriors being a full 15-25%, depending on content, ahead of knights on mitigation before you even factor in disciplines).<br><br>This idea screws knights, doesn't solve the targetted problem (reverse scaling), and it guarantees far meaner mobs in the future that beat down high aggro squishy classes incredibly quickly, like chanters, shammies, clerics, and other essential classes.&nbsp; It also screws rangers for any semblance of a tanking role.<br><div></div>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=175692" target=new>Josahd, Scourge Knight</a>
							</div>
								
