			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=32436'>







<img src="/eq/i/icons/Races/dark_elf.jpg" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=14459#M14459">75</a> of 481
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 716 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			There is a fallacy in your bite reasoning, mana to a cleric does NOT = healing to the tank, in most of the situations you are talking about regardless of what's tanking it's more likely that the tank will die then it is the healer will go out of mana. Let's say a mob has 350 dps, that's not too bad for an xp mob all things concidered, cheal is what 9600 with the aa? that's a cheal roughly every 25-28 seconds to keep up on the mobs dps. That's 960 mana per minute, 96 per tick regen isn't all that hard to pull off in most groups so most clerics could land a cheal every 25 seconds indefinately a good percentage of the time, is they have a 7k mana pool (so easy to get) they can respond to most spikes with quick heals and still keep up. This is assuming casual gear even though casual SKs don't have access to bite of muram. an anguish+ SK with muram is likely grouping with a cleric at 10-11k mana and if they run out of mana on this stuff something is just wrong.<br><br>To BB, Shield Block and overcapped AC is not downward scaling, it's of greater defensive benefit versus high DPS content then it is versus lower DPS content. Shield Block is roughly 4% chance to avoid melee via blocks, now is it more beneficial to avoid 500 damage or 3000? AC is also more useful versus content with greater attack rating and 10% of 350dps is much lower then 10% 700 dps. As far as warriors getting some form of damage avoidance more useful to lower dps/trivial content I really don't have a problem with it nor do I see it as something highly necessary from a class balance standpoint.<br><br>Should a warrior heal like me as a Shadow Knight? No not ever. Warriors excel at the harder hitting content via powerful discs and Knights excel at the weaker hitting content via powerful spells. That's how it should be part of the downside to having powerful SCALING abilities is the absence of power in downward scaling abilities. You can't have agro parity and equal healing and better dps and better tanking or I fail to serve any purpose other then some guy who can pull 5 expansion old content with a green pet and play dead and suck in general. Part of balance actually requires you to be weaker in areas of tanking so that I am needed for something, part of balance also requires me to be weaker in areas of tanking so that you are needed for something. That's roughly the state we are in though content at the high end maybe a bit too leaned towards elaborate events where everything is knight tankable, the gap is still alive and well just less pronounced when nothing kills Knights or challenges warriors significantly.<br><br>This idea of one tank class and 2 3/4 tank classes is extinct, learn to live with it. There are 3 tank classes and there will remain to be 3 tank classes. Each of us has strengths in group content, each has disadvantages. Each of us has raid roles and we excel at those raid roles over the others. Content at times plays to the strengths of one more then the other and that's to be expecting, not every boss is going to be that insanely hard hitter you NEED a warrior on and if it did things would get boring. Likewise not every encounter should be this elaborate script where everything hits weak but amounts to something hard, that gets boring too. Groupwise we are to be interchangeable, Sony has stated this explicitly that any group content is meant to be tankable by all 3 and our natural strengths and weaknesses and the class make up determine our usefulness from group to group. Warriors acting like red-headed stepchildren of EQ are really making things hard on the class in general by asking for rediculous things, just like the knights who asked for a cut and copy of defensive were being rediculous<br><div></div>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=681805"><img src="http://img145.imageshack.us/img145/1867/ninsig3dl.jpg"<br></a><br>The Nameless Server - Level 75 Bloodreaver
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>02-27-2006</span> <span class=time_text>04:38 PM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
